Exercise 6:
The previous exercise violates normalization rules because the category is repeated for each product. To fix this, we can create a separate Category model and set up a one-to-many relationship between Category and Product.

Objective: Create a separate Category model and set up a one-to-many relationship between Category and Product.


This is what I did in Exercise 3: 

rails generate migration AddCategoryToProducts category:references

Going to talk about this in coaching hours.
